{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e7daf797-a54d-439e-a999-e204f511dfa1","content":"Here's your complete migration plan from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP):\n\n---\n\n## Migration Plan: VSTest → Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### Phase 1 — Update Project Files\n\nSince you're already on MSTest 3.8.0, you only need to enable the new runner. Add to a `Directory.Build.props` (or each `.csproj`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Remove** the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package reference from all 5 projects — it's no longer needed with MTP and can cause conflicts.\n\n### Phase 2 — TRX & Code Coverage\n\nAdd these packages to each test project (or via `Directory.Packages.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.6.2\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.13.2\" />\n```\n\n### Phase 3 — Azure DevOps Pipeline\n\nReplace the `VSTest@3` task with `DotNetCoreCLI@2`:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      -- \n      --report-trx\n      --coverage\n      --coverage-output-format cobertura\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Phase 4 — Local Dev Verification\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --report-trx --coverage\n```\n\nEach test project now compiles to an executable — you can also run them directly:\n```bash\n./MyTests --report-trx --coverage\n```\n\n### Key Differences to Be Aware Of\n\n| Concern | Action |\n|---------|--------|\n| `dotnet test` compat | `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport=true` keeps `dotnet test` working |\n| `.runsettings` | Most settings migrate to CLI args (`--` separator); data collectors are replaced by extensions |\n| Parallel projects | `dotnet test` still parallelizes across projects; in-process parallelism uses `[Parallelize]` attribute as before |\n| Filter syntax | `--filter` still works via the compatibility layer |\n\n### Rollout Strategy\n\n1. Migrate one test project first, validate CI end-to-end\n2. Roll out to remaining 4 projects\n3. Remove any leftover `.runsettings` data-collector entries for coverage (now handled by the extension)\n\n---\n\nWant me to generate a sample `Directory.Build.props` or pipeline YAML file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0365199a-749b-4d8f-877f-b1f376863abd","outputTokens":790,"requestId":"BC2C:1554D2:204B56:25BC69:69FA9251"},"id":"cddfd3ac-d6f0-491a-963b-a067ea27b344","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:59:13.698Z","parentId":"bbaf20ab-eeba-4907-860e-d78727c29542"}
